The paper deals with optimization problems related to matching and correspondence, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses various optimization techniques, including semidefinite programming (cs.SD) and quadratic programming (cs.NA), which are relevant subfields of computer science. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on shape matching and image ordering, which are typical applications in machine learning (cs.LG).
